    "Mastropaolo et al. [117] presented an empirical study to investigate whether different but semantically equivalent NL descriptions yield the same code fragments.",
    "The experimental results demonstrate that modifying the description leads to generating different code in approximately 46% of cases.",
    "Furthermore, differences in semantically equivalent descriptions can have an impact on the correctness of the generated code (±28%).",
